The files contained in this archive are the source code for WinWCP.

The have been compiled using Delphi V7.0. 

To install the source code:

Unpack this archive. Two folders (WinWCP and Components) are created within the ..\Borland\Delphi folder.

The Components folder contains a number of components used by WinWCP. These must be installed on the Delphi component toolbar before you open the WinWCP project. 

To install the components:

Add the components folder to the Delphi library path.

Select the Delphi Tools/Environment Options
Select the "Library" panel
Click "..." at the right of Library Path
Add "$(Delphi)\SESComponents" to the library 
Click the Add button.

Add the WinRT component

Select File/Open Project
Select Files of Type "*.dpk"
Select the "Components" Folder
Select "WINRT50"
Click the Install button

Add the SESComponents package of components

Select File/Open Project
Select Files of Type "*.dpk"
Select the "SESComponents" Folder
 Select " SESComponents"
Click the Install button

Open the WinWCP project

Select File/Open Project
Select Files of Type "*.dpr"
Select the "WinWCP" Folder
 Select "WinWCP"
Click the Open button

